WHEREAS, for his three-year career, he has compiled an amazing 9,328 yards and 130
total touchdowns; and
WHEREAS, an even more impressive barometer of Jared's talent is his knack for playing
lights out in big games; and
WHEREAS, he led the NCS Eagles to the 2024 TSSAA Division II-A state championship
with a 12-1 record that was built upon an average of 48 points scored per game and an average
margin of victory of 37 points; and
WHEREAS, in the 2024 BlueCross Bowl, Jared Curtis propelled NCS to the Division II-A
state championship by rushing for 60 yards and four touchdowns and passing for 158 yards and
two additional touchdowns in an incredible display of athletic ability and competitive drive; and
WHEREAS, in less than a week, he led his team to the state championship and won two
major individual awards; and
WHEREAS, a well-rounded and compassionate young man, Jared Curtis has
volunteered in support of the Ronald McDonald House and the Cozy Sock drive that benefits
Vanderbilt Children's Hospital; and
WHEREAS, Jared Curtis has distinguished himself as one of the most gifted football
players and quarterbacks in the nation, and he is richly deserving of our approbation on this
special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we recognize Jared Curtis as an elite quarterback and five-star college
recruit, pay tribute to his exemplary 2024 season in which he led the Nashville Christian School
Eagles to the Division II-A state championship, congratulate him on the many prestigious
awards he has received, and wish him all the best for the 2025 football season.
